*NAME&
        usermgr - manage users

*SYNOPSIS
        usermgr

        usermgr& [@option& [@param& ...]]

*DESCRIPTION
        usermgr& is Monolith's default user management tool, similar in concept and design to the #usermgr& tool from Open Kernel 2.  It supports adding and removing users, either through the command line or an interactive prompt.

        Available *usermgr& commands are listed below. If optional arguments are not specified then *usermgr& will prompt the user.

        *help&
            Displays *usermgr&'s built-in help.

        *add& [?user&] [?cansudo&]
            Adds user ?user&. If ?cansudo& is true, the user can execute the *sudo&(*1&) command.

        *del& [?user&]
            Attempts to delete user ?user&.
